m></a>, an ambitious eight-year project that spanned 30 trips to the world&rsquo;s most pristine territories, land untouched by technology and modern life. Among Salgado&rsquo;s many travels for <em>Genesis</em> was a two-month hike through Ethiopia, spanning 500 miles with 18 pack donkeys and their riders. In the words of Brett Abbott, a Getty Museum curator, Salgado&rsquo;s approach can only be described as &ldquo;epic.&rdquo;</p>"}],"speaker_name":"Sebastião Salgado","tags":["Brazil","activism","environment","global issues","photography"],"title":"The silent drama of photography","video_type":{"id":"1","name":"TED Stage Talk"},"viewed_count":1700918}]}
